stix:STIX_Header.stix:Description:
On October 26, 2020, a trusted third party reported a phishing email from "test@test.com" with the subject "320339814 CD and Payoff Clear to Close".  The email asked the user to click on a link to read a message.  The link, "http://t.com/hud-file/New/Error.php", led to a credential harvesting site which appeared as a fake "Office365.com" login page.

No additional information could be found concerning "arif@knowledgesplice.com". The domain "knowledgesplice.com" appears to belong to Knowledge Splice Service Pvt. Ltd, a company that provides consulting, outsourcing, learning, and technology services.

According to open-source research, "http://t.com/hud-file/New/Error.php" is a media site that has been associated with malicious activity.  At the time of analysis, the URL resolved to the US IP address "1.1.1.1".

This activity was observed in the Healthcare and Public Health Sector.
stix:STIX_Header.stix:Title: IB-20-20057 Malicious Link Led to Credential Harvesting Site
